Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_enable...latch_analysis(25.10)    timing_enable...latch_analysis(25.10)

Name
       timing_enable_multifrequency_latch_analysis

Syntax
        timing_enable_multifrequency_latch_analysis

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       Enables multi-frequency latch timing analysis of the latch time borrow-
       ing  for  when a data signal coming to a latch is controlled by a clock
       with a frequency different to a clock of the latch enabling signal.

       When set to true, the edges of all sending and receiving clocks are an-
       alyzed at every latch, which results in less pessimistic, and more  de-
       tailed timing analysis.

       When  set  to  false, latch time borrowing analysis uses the worst case
       relationship between sending and receiving clocks at the  latch,  which
       can produce paths with pessimistic slack.

       Note:  Enabling  advanced latch analysis can result in some performance
       penalty.

       To set this global variable, use the set_global command.

